        <p class="text-text-light leading-relaxed mb-4"><strong>A <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Decanter_Centrifuge" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-navy font-semibold hover:text-gold transition-colors">decanter centrifuge</a> is an industrial centrifuge that continuously separates solids from liquids. The separation in the decanter occurs due to the high centrifugal force generated by its rotating bowl.</strong></p>
